00:30:50.990 --> 00:30:57.490
So, the structure of an
emblem is a woodcut print

00:30:57.490 --> 00:31:00.050
and then a saying underneath,
so it's a combination.

00:31:00.050 --> 00:31:04.490
The readers are supposed
to reflect upon an image

00:31:04.490 --> 00:31:06.560
and here we have an
image of that's supposed

00:31:06.560 --> 00:31:08.910
to represent a king,
that's power

00:31:08.910 --> 00:31:12.130
but it's also aging terribly
and suffering and it has its paw

00:31:12.130 --> 00:31:16.310
on the world this lion as
it has the crown on its head

00:31:16.310 --> 00:31:22.390
and then underneath, or in
the banner there is a saying,

00:31:22.390 --> 00:31:30.390
and in this case it says: "What
do you think it means to rule?"

00:31:30.390 --> 00:31:35.540
Question, and then the
answer: "To serve while dying".

00:31:35.540 --> 00:31:38.650
So, servir muriendo.

00:31:38.650 --> 00:31:41.230
The emblem turns the table
on the common complaint

00:31:41.230 --> 00:31:45.130
of the abusive power to will
power is to suffer abuse

00:31:45.130 --> 00:31:46.920
in the service of the
common good, it is to give

00:31:46.920 --> 00:31:48.830
up all pleasure and
selfish desires

00:31:48.830 --> 00:31:50.820
to become consumed by sacrifice.

00:31:50.820 --> 00:31:54.090
The face of the lion, like
the steers body is sagging,

00:31:54.090 --> 00:31:57.670
the skin loose and hanging aged
early by the cares of office.

00:31:57.670 --> 00:32:00.170
The front right paw placed
with paternal protection

00:32:00.170 --> 00:32:02.630
over the world is the void
of the violence and fear,

00:32:02.630 --> 00:32:04.780
the great beast's claws
would normally project --

00:32:04.780 --> 00:32:08.140
it radiates instead a
father's benevolence.

00:32:08.140 --> 00:32:12.130
So, then let me go
to another one.

00:32:12.130 --> 00:32:15.220
Covarrubias in the next one
