00:33:17.960 --> 00:33:20.520
In this emblem and let
me find this one here,

00:33:20.520 --> 00:33:25.860
this is over on the left side
here of the page, we're treated

00:33:25.860 --> 00:33:30.530
to inversion of the traditional
moral faetons [phonetic] fall

00:33:30.530 --> 00:33:33.180
rather than a cautionary
tale of the dangers

00:33:33.180 --> 00:33:35.880
of uninhibited ambition of
leaving one's natural station

00:33:35.880 --> 00:33:37.680
in life and flying too high.

00:33:37.680 --> 00:33:40.800
The author of this
wonderful book of emblems,

00:33:40.800 --> 00:33:47.160
Francisco de la Torre, reads
faeton as morally exemplary.

00:33:47.160 --> 00:33:49.490
A self-sacrificing model

00:33:49.490 --> 00:33:53.910
of altruism whose flaming fate
is worthwhile suffering as long

00:33:53.910 --> 00:33:56.670
as the intent was noble.

00:33:56.670 --> 00:33:59.050
So, the theme of self-directed
suffering in the service

00:33:59.050 --> 00:34:01.880
of greater morality is what
we're starting to glean

00:34:01.880 --> 00:34:07.110
from this reframing that's
happening through this group

00:34:07.110 --> 00:34:10.220
of emblems and it's
rampant in Covarrubias,

00:34:10.220 --> 00:34:12.230
especially in the
realm of education

00:34:12.230 --> 00:34:14.960
where the whip is shown in
several cases as being essential

00:34:14.960 --> 00:34:18.610
to the civilization of students,
to their happiness and even

00:34:18.610 --> 00:34:21.980
as in this personalization
of the pedagogy of violence

00:34:21.980 --> 00:34:23.760
to life itself and
that's what you see.

00:34:23.760 --> 00:34:25.740
You see the tools of pedagogy

00:34:25.740 --> 00:34:34.260
and central indent is actually a
whip for flaying peoples' skin.

00:34:34.260 --> 00:34:39.550
So, the emblems motto is: "Dolor
